# Contract Farming ‚Äî premium UI & styling

The product is **operations + analytics** on **phones and tablets in the field** first: farmers, lands, lifecycle, reminders, reports, chat. The UI must feel **premium**, **mobile-first**, and **elegant in dark mode**‚Äîcalm, readable outdoors, and never gimmicky.

## Mobile-first (required)

- **Design and implement for the smallest breakpoint first** (default / `sm`), then enhance for `md` and `lg`. Do not assume hover-only affordances for core actions.
- **Single-column by default**: stack sections, CTAs, and forms vertically; introduce multi-column grids only from `sm:` or `md:` upward.
- **Touch targets**: interactive controls (buttons, list rows, toggles, icon hits) should be at least **~44√ó44px** where feasible‚Äîuse padding on `Button`, `size` variants, or `min-h-11` / `min-h-12` on tappable rows. Keep adequate **spacing between** adjacent tappable elements to prevent mis-taps.
- **Thumb reach**: place primary actions in the **lower half** of full-screen flows when possible (e.g. sticky footer actions for long forms); secondary actions higher or in toolbars.
- **Safe areas**: on full-bleed or fixed bottom UI, account for notches and home indicators: `pb-[max(1rem,env(safe-area-inset-bottom))]`, `pt-[env(safe-area-inset-top)]` where fixed/sticky chrome touches the screen edge.
- **Navigation**: avoid cramming many links in the top bar on narrow widths‚Äîuse **priority + overflow** (primary CTA + menu/sheet) or a **bottom nav** pattern for app-style sections when IA grows. Current `AppTopbar` hides some actions on small screens by design; extend that pattern rather than shrinking text to fit.
- **Tables on mobile**: prefer **cards or stacked rows** at small widths; horizontal scroll for tables only as a last resort, with clear scroll affordance.
- **Performance**: prefer CSS for layout/decoration; avoid heavy blur or large box-shadows on every cell in long lists on low-end devices.

## Dark mode ‚Äî elegance (required)

Dark mode is a **first-class** experience, not an afterthought. **Verify every new screen in `.dark`** (theme toggle).

- **Use tokens only**: `background`, `foreground`, `card`, `border`, `muted`, `muted-foreground`, `primary`, `ring`‚Äînever hard-code `#000` / `#fff` for UI chrome. Elevation comes from **slightly different** `card` vs `background` and **subtle borders**, not from dropping pure black panels everywhere.
- **Borders stay visible**: in dark mode, borders are often **low-contrast white alpha** (`border` token). Do not stack so many nested boxes that borders disappear‚Äîuse **one** clear boundary per level or rely on spacing.
- **Muted text**: `muted-foreground` must stay **readable on `background` and `card`**; if copy feels washed out, fix hierarchy (weight/size) before ad-hoc lighter grays.
- **Primary on dark**: brand moments (`text-primary`, primary buttons, icon wells) should feel **luminous but soft**‚Äîavoid neon saturation; use token `primary` and `/opacity` modifiers (`bg-primary/10`, `ring-primary/15`) for glow-like accents.
- **Decorative layers** (hero grids, radial washes): **lower opacity in `.dark`** than in light so backgrounds stay calm‚Äîe.g. grid `opacity-20` dark vs `opacity-35` light; radial gradients use slightly higher primary alpha only when still subtle.
- **Glass / blur**: `backdrop-blur` + translucent `bg-background/xx` can look great in dark; avoid **extreme** transparency that lets busy content show through behind nav‚Äîkeep **supports-backdrop-filter** fallbacks in mind.
- **Charts**: use **`chart-1`‚Äì`chart-5`**; ensure series and legends remain distinguishable on `card`/`background` in dark (stroke/fill contrast).
- **Images & maps**: prefer dimmed overlays or token-based chrome so light imagery does not blow out dark UI.

## Brand posture

- **Trust + clarity first**; **one accent** (`primary`) per view for brand emphasis.
- **Restraint**: space, hairlines, subtle shadows‚Äînot heavy frames on every widget.

## Tokens (required)

- Semantic variables from `globals.css` / Tailwind‚Äînot raw hex/RGB for theme surfaces.
- **Depth**: `border-border/50`‚Äì`/60`, `shadow-sm`, inset hairlines‚Äîavoid heavy drop shadows on dense data pages.

## Typography

- **Titles**: `font-semibold`‚Äì`font-medium`, `tracking-tight`.
- **Eyebrows**: `text-xs`, uppercase, wide tracking, `text-primary` or `text-muted-foreground`.
- **Body**: `text-sm`‚Äì`text-base`; `tabular-nums` for numeric columns.
- **Micro brand** (e.g. ‚ÄúBy Coldop‚Äù under the title): tiny size + wide tracking + `text-muted-foreground` (avoid shouting all-caps unless the design explicitly requires it).

## Layout & rhythm

- Align marketing width with **`max-w-5xl`** where used; app pages may go full width with **consistent horizontal padding** (`px-4` mobile, `sm:px-6`).
- **Vertical rhythm**: generous `py` on marketing; tighter gaps in data UIs.

## Components & patterns

- **CTAs**: `Button` + `asChild` + `Link`; primary for main action, `outline` / `ghost` for secondary.
- **Cards**: `rounded-xl`, `border border-border`, optional `bg-card/80` + light blur; restrained hover.
- **Icon wells**: `bg-primary/10`, `text-primary`, `ring-1 ring-primary/15`‚Äîaligned with `AppTopbar` mark.

## Motion

- Short transitions (`duration-200`); no distracting motion on tables/forms.

## Accessibility & QA checklist

- **Keyboard + focus**: visible `focus-visible` rings.
- Before shipping UI: **narrow viewport (375px)**, **dark mode on**, and **touch** (or emulator) for primary flows.

## Avoid

- Desktop-only layouts, hover-only critical actions, tiny tap targets, ad-hoc dark grays, loud gradients behind data, decorative noise that fights readability in dark mode.
